product_name: Anastasia Beverly HillsVolumizing Tinted Brow Gel
summary: SummaryHighlightsCruelty FreeThis Anastasia Beverly Hills lightweight, buildable gel color tints and adds volume to your brows for a soft, natural finish that's long-wearing up to 24 hours! The smooth, mousse-like texture and precision brush effortlessly coat each hair, giving brows natural fullness and definition in seconds.
details: DetailsFeaturesLightweight, buildable formula delivers a soft, natural finishWater-resistant and long-wearing up to 24 hoursAdds instant color and volume to brows for natural fullness and definitionMousse-like texture coats each brow hair evenly from root to tipCustom-designed, precision, dual-action brush features long and short bristlesBrush fits perfectly in the brow for an easy, mess-free applicationStays true to color as it applies, blends, and setsQuick-drying formula allows time for blending before settingIdeal for fine, light-colored, and patchy browsCan be used to cover grey hairs and color-correctingPerfect for beginners or on-the-go browsVersatile shade range features warm, cool, and neutral tonesDermatologist testedFree of: Phthalates, Mineral Oil, Alcohol, Talc, Sulfates, Parabens, FragranceItem 2627709How To UseWipe off excess product before applying. Using the long bristle side, start by applying at the highest point of the brow and work towards the end. Using the remaining product, apply to the front and blend throughout the brow to create desired color and volume. Use the short bristle side to add extra definition and detail. Let it dry 20 seconds before blending or layering additional product.PRO TIPS:Use light pressure when applying on brow hair.Select a shade closest to your natural hair color.Backcomb to build volume.IngredientsIsododecane, Mica, Macadamia Seed Oil Polyglyceryl-6 Esters Behenate, Isodecyl Neopentanoate, Microcrystalline Wax/Cera Microcristallina/Cire Microcristalline, Synthetic Fluorphlogopite, C10-18 Trigylcerides, Hydrogenated Soybean Oil, Hydrogenated Polycyclopentadiene, Silica, Copernicia Cerifera (Carnauba) Wax/Cera Carnauba/Cire De Carnauba, Trimethylsiloxysilicate, Sorbitan Olivate, Synthetic Wax, Sorbitan Isostearate, Hydrogenated Styrene/Isoprene Copolymer, Dimethicone, Tocopherol, Caprylyl Glycol, Glycerin, Water/Aqua/Eau, Pentaerythrityl Tetra-Di-T-Butyl Hydroxyhydrocinnamate, Cucurbita Pepo (Pumpkin) Seed Oil, Helianthus Annuus (Sunflower) Seed Oil, Saccharide Isomerate, Butylene Glycol, Adansonia Digitata Seed Oil, Rosa Canina Fruit Oil, Ceramide Np, Macadamia Integrifolia Seed Oil, Vitis Vinifera (Grape) Seed Oil, Polyglyceryl-3 Diisostearate, Carthamus Tinctorius (Safflower) Flower Extract, Hibiscus Sabdariffa Flower Extract, Phytosphingosine, Camellia Sinensis Leaf Extract, Epilobium Angustifolium Flower/Leaf/Stem Extract, Hydrogenated Lecithin, Hippophae Rhamnoides Oil, Ribes Nigrum (Black Currant) Seed Oil, Citric Acid, Sodium Citrate, Phenoxyethanol, Titanium Dioxide (CI 77891), Iron Oxides (CI 77491, CI 77492, CI 77499).Shipping & Coupon RestrictionsThis brand is excluded from most Ulta Beauty coupons.See brand eligibility details

reviews.headline: Worst brush
reviews.comments: The brush looks so short I thought I had a faulty product but evidently this is what the brush looks like according to the picture. Wish I had noticed that before buying it. It was difficult to use and made me look like a clown.

reviews.headline: Amazing product!  I hope they make this forever!
reviews.comments:
This is the best ever in covering gray and white brow hairs.  It goes on easy, doesn't glop, and you don't need to use much to cover those stubborn grays/whites.  The unique brush is fabulous at allowing you to easily reach and cover all the brow hairs, not just those on the surface.  This is the product I've been looking for!!!
I never write reviews, ever, but wanted to share this with others in the quest to cover those pesky gray and white brows.

reviews.headline: Long lasting, intense color.
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] The product is great long last, but I prefer the pencil, it's a bit easier to work with. Maybe I'll try different techniques. I would recommend

reviews.headline: Not Happy
reviews.comments: Years ago I used to love this product because of the color and staying power.....however, they've since redesigned the "brush" to more like a comb. If you have decent, or thick eyebrows, you may love this newer design, but the reason I need to do my brows everyday, is because they're light white to blonde and scarce. I need a duo pair, gel and fill liner, in a taupe, to fill and darken the hairs. Now it's more like a tiny comb with the other side being practically no bristles at all. It's also shorter than most brow brushes. With my brows, this brush is TERRIBLE! Maybe it's great for people with fuller dark brows in the first place, but I'll be shopping for a different one for sure!!

reviews.headline: Great product
reviews.comments: I received this product in exchange for my honest review. I have never used an ABH brow product before, this product is great. It lasts all day and comes through with pigment.

reviews.headline: 2nd purchase of this item but in a different shade
reviews.comments: I do love the ease with which the gel goes on my eyebrows; however, I am not thrilled that the shape of the brush has been changed, making it much tinier - I have no idea why this adjustment was necessary & hopefully, they will increase its size.

reviews.headline: Takes some practice
reviews.comments: I found this product a bit difficult to use at first because its much more pigmented than my go-to brow gel. However, after more practice with the product, I've grown to like it a lot more. It definitely gives my brows a deeper color and the illusion of greater thickness. Wouldn't use it for everyday or no makeup makeup looks though

reviews.headline: Quick Brows
reviews.comments: I bought this spontaneously when I went to Ulta a few weeks ago. I love how easy it is to get full eyebrows. I have been on a hunt for makeup products that make it easy for tossing in my makeup bag for on the go. This is one of them!

reviews.headline: Love this
reviews.comments: I tried this in the store and had to have it. I was using a pensil for the longest time, made the switch to this. It makes my eyebrows look natural, full and stays on all day.

reviews.headline: Nice packaging, small pencil, great quality
reviews.comments: This works like the Benefit Brow & Tinted that I have. It has a micro precise brow pencil which make it easy to apply on my eyebrow. I love the packaging. Very pretty and elegant and unique, because we can see the shade righr away. The only thing is because I dont have much brows, so when I put it on, it doesnt thicken that much. But overall, I like this product. I just need to draw with a pencil first and put this on as a second coat.

reviews.headline: Love this formula and brush!
reviews.comments: I absolutely love how this formula worked with my eyebrows. It color matched great with my natural eyebrow color. The brush is perfect. The formula was r flaky after it dried and it lasted all day. I love this product and would recommend to a friend.

reviews.headline: A favorite
reviews.comments: Ive used it three times already and can confirm its better then what ive used before. Ive tried the nyx bro glue laminating and the anastasia dipbrow. The applicator gives my brow a natural look and its the right shade. I have sparsed areas in my eyebrow and this helps cover them up that i dont have to go in with my brow pencil as much.

reviews.headline: Quick Dry Formula
reviews.comments: Gel formula is a bit too thick and dark for my personal liking. I've found that I have to apply it lightly and sparingly in order for my brows to remain with a natural look. On a positive note, it dries fast and seems to be waterproof.

reviews.headline: Lightweight and buildable tint
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] This tinted brow gel is a game-changer! Lightweight, buildable, and smudge-proof, it fills in brows effortlessly while keeping them natural. The spoolie ensures precise application, and the color lasts all day. Quick, easy, and totally worth it!

reviews.headline: Do not recommend
reviews.comments: I had the old Anastasia brow gel and this color was identical but the formula isn't what it used to be. Really disappointed.

reviews.headline: Applicator is Awful
reviews.comments: I have always used Anastasia for my eyebrows. I have thick dark brows and a gel wand is what works best for me. At some point, Anastasia discontinued the old product I used, which was a standard mascara wand applicator. I has to switch to this, and it is so messy! I have to clean up my brows with Q-tips every time I use this and it's so expensive that I can't bring myself to get rid of it. Very disappointing.

reviews.headline: The formula is different and the brush is awful.
reviews.comments: I do not like the way that the formula has been redone. It is dry and smears easily, and the brush is lopsided intentionally, but that causes issues with distributing the product.

reviews.headline: Great color
reviews.comments:
[I received this product in exchange for my honest review]

 I really love this brow gel.  It's dark enough where I don't have to fill in my brows with a pencil or powder. They stay put and last all day long. I love the different length sides of the spoolie.

reviews.headline: Will be buying more of this product
reviews.comments: This is a perfect color for blondes/gray hair brows. It covers the gray hairs nicely. Love this product.

faceoff_positive.comments:
The Volumeizing Tinted Brow Gel in the shade Ebony is a fantastic product for anyone looking to enhance their brows with both definition and fullness. Here's a detailed review highlighting its key features and performance:

**Formula and Texture**: The gel has a lightweight yet creamy texture that glides on smoothly without feeling heavy or sticky. It effectively coats each brow hair, providing a natural-looking finish that doesn't clump or flake throughout the day.

**Color Payoff**: The Ebony shade is rich and pigmented, making it perfect for those with dark hair. It adds depth and dimension to the brows while still allowing for a soft, natural look. The color blends seamlessly with natural brow hairs, avoiding that harsh, drawn-on appearance.

**Application**: The applicator wand is designed for precision, featuring a small brush that allows for easy maneuverability, even in the tiniest areas. This makes it simple to fill in sparse spots and shape the brows without overloading the product.

**Longevity**: One of the standout features of this brow gel is its staying power. It holds brows in place throughout the day, resisting smudging or fading even in humid conditions. Whether you're at work or out for a night on the town, your brows will look as good at the end of the day as they did when you first applied the gel.

**Overall Impression**: The Volumeizing Tinted Brow Gel in Ebony is a must-have for those looking to achieve fuller, well-defined brows. Its blend of color, hold, and ease of application makes it a standout product in the brow category. Whether you're a makeup novice or a seasoned pro, this gel will elevate your brow game with minimal effort. Highly recommended!
faceoff_positive.headline: Love it

faceoff_negative.comments: If you look at this product while it's on someone from a few feet away it looks normal, once you get within a face to face or actually look at yourself in the mirror this is a truly terrible product. It is the most obvious 'filled' looking brow product I've ever seen. It doesn't blend smoothly, sticks the existing brow hairs reflecting light to really highlight what's there. It looks crazy, like you just tried doing your makeup for the first time. I even tried to spoolie it out to remove some of the harshness of the look and it did nothing. The applicator shape makes no sense- I had to clean up the edges with a q-tip just to cope. I then sat home doing nothing for hours only to look in the mirror and see how it was wearing away. I had been FaceTiming and it looked totally normal on camera but up close in personâ€¦YIKES. Hate this product, so glad I don't just trust it before going out somewhere. I've been using ABH products for well over a decade but I think benefit may finally get me after how terrible the two brow gels are. Sad because the pomade or the dip brown gel were my absolute must haves. Returning ASAP. I posted this review elsewhere to spread the word and because I'm too lazy to rewrite.
